verses.roman:
govardhanera putra teṅho, nāma--'raghunātha'
nīlācale paricaya āche tomāra sātha?"

synonyms: govardhanera—of Govardhana; putra—the son; teṅho—he; nāma—named; raghunātha—Raghunātha dāsa; nīlācale—in Nīlācala; paricaya āche—is there acquaintance; tomāra sātha—with you.
translation: "That person is Raghunātha dāsa, the son of Govardhana Majumadāra. Did you meet him in Nīlācala?"
